This paper discusses the use of reputation and trust-based systems for wireless self-organizing networks, which are primarily studied in the computer science subfield of network and internet security (cs.NI) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the working principles and effectiveness of different reputation systems, which involves the use of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of reputation systems for evaluating the trustworthiness of nodes, which involves the use of machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses open problems in the area of reputation and trust-based systems, which is a topic of interest in the field of social networks and computational social science (cs.SI).
